According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Management Consulting Services Market was valued at USD 176.2 billion in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 273.3 billion by 2034, expanding at a CAGR of 5.0% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing sustained growth as organizations across industries accelerate digital transformation initiatives, strengthen operational resilience, and adapt to increasingly complex regulatory environments. The growing demand for strategic advisory, AI-driven business transformation, ESG consulting, cybersecurity planning, and operational optimization is encouraging enterprises to partner with consulting firms that can deliver measurable business outcomes while supporting long-term organizational growth.
